<DOC><DOCNO> AP890221-0292 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-21-89 1934EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-IBMComputers     02-21 0139</FIRST><SECOND>AM-IBM Computers,0144</SECOND><HEAD>IBM Announces Upgrades Of Mid-Size Computers</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   International Business Machines Corp. on Tuesdayannounced improvements to its Application System-400 line ofmid-size computers, which it is using as a weapon in a war formarket share with Digital Equipment Corp.   IBM announced expansion features for the smallest models of theAS-400 line _ the B10 and B20 _ and a new B70 that extends the rangeof the line. They will be available in June.   IBM introduced the first six models of the AS-400 line with greatfanfare in June 1988. It announced more than 1,000 programs thatwould run on the machines, a number that it said has since grown tomore than 4,000.   The price of the B70 is about $400,000, includingoperating-system software and a 16-megabyte main memory card.</TEXT></DOC>